<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" CalDefCategory="Tuner" Description="This cal file defines the DAB Tuner calibrations beginning in MY18.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>21</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>May 09, 2014</Date>
    <Description>The following changes have been made to this release.  Since DAB is My18 content, this file represents work in progress.  GME and Harman are reviewing this feature.  Updates will be made as necessary.  Deleted DAB_StationListUpdateRate, StationListUpdateRate, and StrongStationUpdateRate as they are not applicable for Info 3.  Changed cal names to CamelCase.  Deleted DAB Station List, StrongStationList and Details cals as they are not relevant for Info 3. </Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>18Aug2014</Date>
    <Description>This change comprehends reallocation of some DAB related cals from the tunerHMI caldef file to this document to better align tuner and HMI cal functions.  These decisions were made based on joint GM/Harman reviews.Cals that have been moved are at the Rev 3 level in the individual cal change logs.</Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>29SEP14</Date>
    <Description>Add Usage on all components</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>December 1, 2014</Date>
    <Description>Release File Change Log:  Cal Def File Version 5.  December 2, 2014
Here is a summary of the changes for this release based on reviews with Harman:

1.  DAB_DAB_LinkDABSearchStartTime.  Upper limit is incorrect at 255.  Should be 3500 so that it is within range for default setting of 3000.</Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>2/26/2015</Date>
    <Description>Confirmed with Alan Budyta the max value of DAB_DAB_LinkDABSearchStartTime cal within this caldef should be changed from 255 to 3500. Now the default value fits within the cal range.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>24.03.2015</Date>
    <Description>The following calibration changes were made for the April 15th release:&#xD;
&#xD;
1.  Added enumdef file (GIS655_DABTuner.enumdef) to DABTuner caldef to support DAB Band III selection for world markets. And, as a result added the following three new enumeration type CALs to this CALDef file:  DAB_DABFrequencyBand, DAB_DefaultChannel, and DAB_UserSetting_AnnouncementFilter.&#xD;

2.  Added cal params for DAB_EnableSlideShow.&#xD;

3.  Added DAB_SlideshowMinDisplayTime to match requirements in GIS-502.&#xD;

4.  Updated DAB_AnnouncementActive description to remove references to Intellitext as this feature is not supported in DAB.  Also clarified usage of this calibration in the tuner.

5.  Removed the DAB_Intellitext_Active cal as the Info 3 Program will not be supporting Intellitext.

The following cal decriptions have been modified to address Assembla Ticket #1708:

6.  Modified the description for DAB to DAB linking to reference both the tuner enable/disable state with the associated HMI menu items required to support the feature.

7.  Modified the description for DAB to FM linking to reference both the tuner enable/disable state with the associated HMI menu items required to support the feature.

8.  Modified the description for DAB Announcements to reference both the tuner enable/disable state with the associated HMI menu items required to support the feature.



</Description>
    <Author>Christian Gross</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>26.05.2015</Date>
    <Description>Deleted DAB_TuningMsgTime (moved to HMI side), deleted DAB_FastSeekTuneRate (moved to HMI side), deleted DisplayDABCategories (moved to HMI)</Description>
    <Author>Christian Gro&#xdf;</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>08.06.2015</Date>
    <Description>Readded &quot;DAB_FastSeekTuneRate&quot; cal based on feedback given by Alan Budyta.</Description>
    <Author>Christian Gro&#xdf;</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>24JUN2015</Date>
    <Description>The following changes have been implemented in this release:&#xD;
1. Added DAB_EnableAlbumArt cal as both DAB Slideshow and DAB Album Art need to be treated separatetly.  As such, the description for DAB_Slideshow changed to reflect the slideshow feature and DAB_EnableAlbumArt added to support the DAB Album Art feature.&#xD;
&#xD;
2.  Clarified the descriptions for DAB_EnableDAB, DAB_EnableSlideShow, DAB_EnableAlbumArt, DAB_EnableEPG, and DAB_EnableTPEG to clarify tuner and HMI expected behavior based on the status of these cals.  Specifically, disabling any of these cals means the tuner shall no longer process the feature AND any associated HMI menu items shall be removed to effectively eliminate the feature from the vehicle.  This helps balance system resources in the tuner and the overall system.  Alternatively, enabling the calibrations means the tuner shall perform the associated processing to enable the feature and HMI shall provide the associated menu items for the end user.  This implies once the HMI  menu item is enabled, HMI menu item cals in GIS-502 caldef determine the associated default state (on/off, enable/disable,etc).</Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>2015-July-21</Date>
    <Description>Adding Mute and Fade Cals back in per 2015-July-20 memo from Alan and Sanghyun Ryu.  These cals are supplier specific and required to support the LOW radio when seamless DAB linking is not supported. These are the calibrations that were added:

SS_MuteFadeInEFCThreshold_EEPxB
SS_MuteFadeInEFCThreshold_EEPxA
SS_MuteFadeOutEFCThreshold_EEPxB
SS_MuteFadeOutEFCThreshold_EEPxA
SS_MuteFadeInEFCThreshold_UEPX
SS_MuteFadeOutEFCThreshold_UEPX
SS_MuteBERAverageFactor
</Description>
    <Author>Kiran Soni</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>3/8/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef file added a new calibration called DAB_OK_TrafficNGo for Low Radio usage only. This calibration is being added per final email correspondence request from GMK, GME, and GMNA teams on 3/2/2016 for the following reason: New request for this calibration from LGE regarding DAB-FM linking scenario based on PRTS/ESIMS issue in their BYOM2 project. The background is: Opel validation engineer requested wheel speed calibration to make stay in FM at traffic condition(No significant signal change) to minimize audio mute during DAB-FM transition. Info3.0 support seamless linking so we expect less audio mute than BYOM2. However, it`s not verified in field test yet so LGE wants this calibration as a prevention in case they have same issue.  </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>3/18/2016</Date>
    <Description>This release includes the following changes.  The impact is for High/Mid only:&#xD;
      1.  The following calibrations are deleted as they are not required for the High/Mid and had no usage on the LOW:  &#xD;
      DAB_FM_LinkingFMQualityAvgFactor&#xD;
      DAB_FM_LinkingFMQualityHysteresis&#xD;
&#xD;
      2.  The following calibrations have Usage changes from High Mid Low to Low Only:    DAB_DAB_LinkDABSignalGoodTime&#xD;
      DAB_SLFM_Link_DABOkThreshold&#xD;
      DAB_SLFM_Link_DABSignalGoodTime&#xD;
&#xD;
      3.  The following calibrations have been added as supplier specific (SS_) calibrations specific for High Mid Usage only:&#xD;
      DAB_DAB_LinkDABOkAltThreshold&#xD;
      DAB_SLFM_Link_DABOkAltThreshold&#xD;
      FM_DAB_Hysteresis_Timer&#xD;
      FM_DAB_PI_Lost_Hysterisis&#xD;
&#xD;
&#xD;
    </Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>14</Version>
    <Date>03/22/2016</Date>
    <Description>The following DAB.caldef changes are defined for Version 14 as Harman SS_ (supplier specific) calibrations for linking hysteresis:
   SS_DAB_DAB_Ensemble_Quality_Threshold_Current
   SS_DAB_DAB_Ensemble_Quality_Threshold_Alternative
   SS_DAB_FM_Ensemble_Quality_Threshold_Current
   SS_DAB_FM_Audio_Quality_Threshold_Alternative
   SS_FM_DAB_Audio_Quality_Threshold_Current
   SS_FM_DAB_Ensemble_Quality_Threshold_Alternative</Description>
    <Author>Christian Gross</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>15</Version>
    <Date>2016-Jun-07</Date>
    <Description>As per CR# 1053505 removed Non-seamless linking cals. removed CAL_NSLFMLink_DABWeakThreshold,CAL_NSLFMLink_DABOkThreshold,CAL_NSLFMLink_DABSignalGoodTime. As these are not needed for DAB radios due to all DAB radios have implemented seamless linking. </Description>
    <Author>Kiran Soni</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>16</Version>
    <Date>Dec. 06, 2016</Date>
    <Description>Deleted SS_DAB_SLFM_Link_DABOkAltThreshold, SS_DAB_DAB_LinkDABOkAltThreshold, DAB_FM_LinkingFMQualityThreshold; changed usage to mid/high for following parameters: DAB_DAB_LinkDABOkThreshold, DAB_SLFM_Link_DABWeakThreshold; changed default value of DAB_SeekStopBIII to 50.999 based on Harman recommendation; Changed type DAB_UserSetting_AnnouncementFilter cal from enum to Integer Array to have the possibility to select more than one filter category. Per default, all filters are set to 1=true. </Description>
    <Author>Christian Gro&#xdf;</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>17</Version>
    <Date>2017-Feb-08</Date>
    <Description>Removing the Interger Array : DAB_UserSetting_AnnouncementFilter. Adding back Enum (same as what was in Ver 15) : DAB_UserSetting_AnnouncementFilter</Description>
    <Author>Kiran Soni</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>18</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>19</Version>
    <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS655_DABTuner.caldef file, added GEM usage to all of the calibrations within this caldef, except for the following ten calibrations within this caldef file: 1.) SS_FM_DAB_Ensemble_Quality_Threshold_Alternative, 2.) SS_FM_DAB_Audio_Quality_Threshold_Current, 3.) SS_DAB_FM_Audio_Quality_Threshold_Alternative, 4.) SS_DAB_FM_Ensemble_Quality_Threshold_Current, 5.) SS_DAB_DAB_Ensemble_Quality_Threshold_Alternative, 6.) SS_DAB_DAB_Ensemble_Quality_Threshold_Current, 7.) SS_FM_DAB_PI_Lost_Hysteresis, 8.) SS_FM_DAB_Hysteresis_Timer, 9.) DAB_EnableEPG, and 10.) DAB_EnableTPEG.  Note, did not add GEM usage for these  ten calibrations since these ten calibraions did not fall within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>20</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>21</Version>
    <Date>6/19/2019</Date>
    <Description>Per CR# 2303128 AOSP transition, in MY22 GIS-646 Cal DB V6.0.3 deprecating the following cals: DAB_SlideShowMinDisplayTime, DAB_EnableAlbumArt, DAB_EnableSlideShow, DAB_EnableEPG, DAB_EnableTPEG, DAB_FastSeekTuneRate.</Description>
    <Author>Christine Marzan</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="When it is in FM linking, if wheel speed is under this value, DAB fallback is not conducted but also it stays in FM linking." Name="DAB_OK_TrafficNGo" References="GIS-655" Usage="LOW,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_6_kcEOaiEeWS6bElCetEBg</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>3/8/2016</Date>
      <Description>Initial release of this calibration</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Integer>
      <Value>20</Value>
      <MinValue>0</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>255</MaxValue>
      <Units>km_per_hour</Units>
      <Resolution>1.0</Resolution>
    </Integer>
  </CalDefinition>
