  <CalDefinition Description="The DAB_DAB_LinkingActive cal defines whether DAB to DAB linking shall be enabled in the tuner and whether or not the associated HMI menu item(s) associated with this feature should be displayed. TRUE means enable DAB to DAB linking in the tuner and display the associated DAB to DAB Linking menu item(s). FALSE means disable DAB to DAB linking in the tuner and disable HMI display of the associated DAB to DAB Linking menu item(s). The default value is TRUE. The tuner shall also take appropriate action to support/not support the processing of this feature based on the cal setting. This helps balance and optimize system resources based on activated features for a given market." Name="DAB_DAB_LinkingActive" References="GIS-699-031900 DAB Default Settings" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_94SNIScAEeSmb8tw1ZVRMw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
