  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="The DAB_EnableDAB calibration defines whether all HMI menu items associated with DAB and the associated DAB tuner processing should be enabled/disabled for a specific region. TRUE means display enabled DAB HMI menu item(s) and activate DAB processing in the Tuner. FALSE means do not display any DAB related HMI menu item(s) and do not activate DAB processing in the tuner. The default value is TRUE. The tuner shall also take appropriate action to support/not support the processing of this feature based on the cal setting. This helps balance and optimize system resources based on activated features for a given market." Name="DAB_EnableDAB" References="GIS-699-031000 DAB Activation" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
