  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="The DAB_EnableAlbumArt calibration defines whether the HMI menu item associated with DAB_EnableAlbumArt and the associated tuner processing should be enabled/disabled for a specific region. TRUE means display the DAB_EnableAlbumArt HMI menu item(s) and activate DAB_EnableAlbumArt processing in the Tuner. FALSE means do not display the DAB_EnableAlbumArt HMI menu item(s) and do not activate DAB_EnableAlbumArt processing in the tuner. The default value is TRUE. The tuner shall also take appropriate action to support/not support the processing of this feature based on the cal setting. This helps balance and optimize system resources based on activated features for a given market." Name="DAB_EnableAlbumArt" References="GIS-699-030810 Album Art and Station Logos (Slideshow)" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
