  <CalDefinition Description="The DAB_EnableSlideShow calibration defines whether the HMI menu item associated with DAB_EnableSlideShow and the associated tuner processing should be enabled/disabled for a specific region. TRUE means display the DAB_EnableSlideShow HMI menu item(s) and activate DAB_EnableSlideShow processing in the Tuner. FALSE means do not display the DAB_EnableSlideShow HMI menu item(s) and do not activate DAB_EnableSlideShow processing in the tuner. The default value is TRUE. A False setting helps balance system resources by removing tuner processing of this feature and the associated HMI." Name="DAB_EnableSlideShow" References="GIS-699-030810 Album Art and Station Logos (Slideshow)" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
