  <CalDefinition Description="The DAB_EnableEPG calibration defines whether HMI menu items associated with DAB EPG and the associated DAB EPG tuner processing should be enabled/disabled for a specific region. TRUE means display enabled DAB EPG HMI menu item(s) and activate DAB EPG processing in the Tuner. FALSE means do not display any DAB EPG related HMI menu item(s) and do not activate DAB EPG processing in the tuner. The default value is FALSE. The tuner shall also take appropriate action to support/not support the processing of this feature based on the cal setting. This helps balance and optimize system resources based on activated features for a given market." Name="DAB_EnableEPG" References="GIS-316-3300 Electronic Program Guide " Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
